                            <comment id="12914421" author="srowen" created="Fri, 24 Sep 2010 12:39:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Seeing no progress yet, and that this is an improvement, I don&apos;t think we&apos;d hold up an imminent 0.4 over this. I know Robin has other stuff to look at.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12929663" author="ppeddi" created="Mon, 8 Nov 2010 18:31:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We are currently using Weka&apos;s FPGrowth that supports most of the above params. But since Weka is not distributed, I am looking into mahout&apos;s PFPGrowth. Options like minimum and maximum # of items per item set is very important for us since we are only interested in generated product to product association rules. Suporting this will reduce the # of items to load and could potentially reduce both memory and increase the speed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I see that the target fix release for this is 0.5. Is it still planned for 0.5 and if so, when is the 0.5 release scheduled?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12984074" author="srowen" created="Thu, 20 Jan 2011 08:17:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cleaning house and updating some issues &amp;#8211; Robin, perhaps you can catch up on these issues as they pertain to your areas.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no plan for 0.5 but probably May. The best thing is to provide a patch implementing these params.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13000843" author="srowen" created="Tue, 1 Mar 2011 11:50:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Praveen, if you&apos;d like to supply a patch, that&apos;s great. Otherwise I think we will mark this as won&apos;t-fix as of 0.5 since nobody seems to be taking it up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13013977" author="srowen" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 14:52:24 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;No work in a year... looks like a won&apos;t fix? Robin committed something related to this a while ago but I don&apos;t see how it&apos;s related.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
